23:25.559 --> 23:27.260
It's okay.

23:30.363 --> 23:32.966
SALLY? KATHERYN CRYER.

23:32.966 --> 23:35.569
CAN I SPEAK TO DAVID,
PLEASE?

23:35.569 --> 23:36.803
ALL RIGHT.

23:36.803 --> 23:39.540
HAVE HIM CALL ME WHEN HE GETS
OFF THE BENCH, OKAY?

23:39.540 --> 23:42.843
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

23:42.843 --> 23:45.411
I WILL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

23:45.411 --> 23:46.713
THANK YOU.

23:49.249 --> 23:52.619
NOW YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHY YOUR BAGS ARE PACKED?

23:52.619 --> 23:55.455
BECAUSE WE'RE GOING
ON VACATION TODAY.

23:55.455 --> 23:56.590
WHO'S WE?

23:56.590 --> 23:58.124
YOU AND I.

23:58.124 --> 23:59.860
‐BUT MS. CRYER ‐‐
‐WE LEAVE IN AN HOUR.

23:59.860 --> 24:01.267
MS. CRYER,
I CAN'T GO NOWHERE.

24:01.267 --> 24:04.037
MY BABY'S IN JAIL.
I CAN'T LEAVE.

24:04.037 --> 24:06.773
BUT YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:06.773 --> 24:09.342
I NEED YOU.

24:09.342 --> 24:11.377
[ SIGHS ]

24:11.377 --> 24:13.580
WELL, HOW FAR AWAY
WILL WE BE?

24:13.580 --> 24:16.082
IN TOWN.

24:16.082 --> 24:17.450
EXCUSE ME?

24:17.450 --> 24:18.519
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

24:18.519 --> 24:20.854
THE CHEMO'S
NOT WORKING, OKAY?

24:23.824 --> 24:28.695
I'M SCHEDULED FOR SURGERY
IN THE MORNING.

24:28.695 --> 24:30.764
THEY'RE GOING TO
REMOVE MY BREAST.

24:30.764 --> 24:39.773
♪♪♪♪

24:39.773 --> 24:41.441
MRS. CRYER...

24:41.441 --> 24:44.377
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

24:44.377 --> 24:45.646
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

24:45.646 --> 24:47.648
YOU SHOULD TELL YOUR FAMILY.

24:47.648 --> 24:49.983
WHY?

24:49.983 --> 24:51.985
SO THEY CAN WARM UP MY WILL?

24:51.985 --> 24:56.056
